The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems, which are a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). It also draws on optimization in operations research (cs.NE) and applies approximation structures (cs.SY) to solutions of constraint satisfaction problems. The use of semantics of conjunctions of atomic formulas of predicate logic (cs.LO) further supports these likely categories.
